Parliament, Monday 13 February 2023 – The Joint Sitting of the National Assembly (NA) and the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will debate the President’s State of the Nation Address (SONA) tomorrow, Tuesday 14 February at 10.00. The SONA debate, to be held at the Cape Town City Hall, will resume again on Wednesday at 14,00.
	President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to reply to the debate on his SONA on Thursday at 14.00.
	
	Details of tomorrow’s Joint Sitting are as follows:
	Date: Tuesday 14 February 2023Venue: Cape Town City Hall
	
	Note to media
	
	Members of the Media must use the same Accreditation Tags issued to them for SONA 2023 to gain access to the Cape Town City Hall. Queries on access to the venue must be sent to Mr Mlindi Mpindi at mmpindi@parliament.gov.za or 081 716 7329.
	
	
	Members of the media who wish to observe the Parliament sittings on a virtual platform should forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared. Journalists must forward their requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the proceedings live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via the live stream on Parliament’s YouTube channel, Facebook and Twitter pages. Please see links below.
	
	You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notifications of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAEnquiries: Moloto Mothapo The copy of an Act of Parliament signed by the President is the official version of that Act and is given to the Constitutional Court for safekeeping. African National Congress on the provincial list for the province of Gauteng